functionDecorators.name: getEstimatedTokensForETH
functionDecorators.description: Calculation of the number of tokens that you need to spend to get _ethAmount.

parameterDecorators.name: _token
parameterDecorators.description: - The address of the token that we exchange for ETH.

parameterDecorators.name: _ethAmount
parameterDecorators.description: - The amount of ETH to be received.

returnDecorators.description: The number of tokens you need to get ETH.

functionDecorators.name: owner
functionDecorators.description: Returns the address of the current owner.

functionDecorators.name: renounceOwnership
functionDecorators.description: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

parameterDecorators.name: _token
parameterDecorators.description: - The address of the token that we exchange for ETH.

parameterDecorators.name: _receiveEthAmount
parameterDecorators.description: - The exact amount of ETH to be received.

parameterDecorators.name: _tokensMaxSpendAmount
parameterDecorators.description: - The maximum number of tokens allowed to spend.

parameterDecorators.name: _ethReceiver
parameterDecorators.description: - The wallet address to send ETH to after the exchange.

parameterDecorators.name: _tokensReceiver
parameterDecorators.description: - Wallet address, to whom to send the remaining unused tokens from the exchange.

functionDecorators.name: transferOwnership
functionDecorators.description: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
